袭击一年内，五角大楼受损部分重建并进驻人员。<ref>{{cite news |last=Oglesby |first=Christy |title=Phoenix rises: Pentagon honors 'hard-hat patriots' |url=http://archives.cnn.com/2002/US/09/11/ar911.memorial.pentagon/ |publisher=CNN |date=2002-09-11 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20041218040531/http://archives.cnn.com/2002/US/09/11/ar911.memorial.pentagon/ |archivedate=2004-12-18 |accessdate=2014-05-29 }}</ref>2003年末，临时[[世界贸易中心车站_(PATH)|世界贸易中心车站]]开放，新的世贸中心7号塔重建并于2006年完工。世贸中心主址重建後延至2006年末，直至承租人[[拉里·希尔弗斯坦|拉里·希尔弗斯坦]]和纽约与新泽西港务局在财务上取得同意才得继续。最終[[丹尼尔·里伯斯金|丹尼尔·里伯斯金]]设计的「{{link-en|紀念之基|Memory Foundations}}」（{{lang|en|Memory Foundations}}）被选为基本方案，其中包括一座541米高的[[世界貿易中心一號大樓|新一號樓]]、三座沿教堂街的办公楼、以及{{link-en|麥可·艾拉德|Michael Arad}}设计的纪念馆。<ref>{{cite news |url=https://select.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=F20913F63A550C718EDDA00894DE404482 |title=An Agreement Is Formalized on Rebuilding at Ground Zero |work=The New York Times |last=Bagli |first=Charles V. |date=2006-09-22 |accessdate=2011-09-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111219044353/http://select.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=F20913F63A550C718EDDA00894DE404482 |archive-date=2011-12-19 |dead-url=no }}</ref>2006年4月27日，[[世界貿易中心一號大樓|新一號樓]]开始重建，2013年5月20日盖到最高。当日，塔尖安装後的该楼高度达到1,776英尺（541米），成为西半球最高的建筑。<ref>{{cite news|url = http://www.nydailynews.com/new-york/1-wtc-spire-bringing-full-height-article-1.1340224|title = One World Trade Center gets spire, bringing it to its full 1,776-foot height|last = Badia|first = Erik|date = 2013-05-10|work = New York Daily News website|access-date = 2015-01-12|last2 = Sit|first2 = Ryan|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20170204064716/http://www.nydailynews.com/new-york/1-wtc-spire-bringing-full-height-article-1.1340224|archive-date = 2017-02-04|dead-url = no}}</ref>2014年11月3日，世界贸易中心一号大楼竣工开放。<ref name="MooreOneWTC">{{cite web |last=Moore |first=Jack |title=World Trade Center Re-opens as Tallest Building in America |url=http://onewtc.com/news/world-trade-center-re-opens-as-tallest-building-in-america |publisher=世界貿易中心一號大樓 |work=[[国际财经时报|国际财经时报]] |date=2014-11-03 |accessdate=2015-09-11 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150904120549/http://onewtc.com/news/world-trade-center-re-opens-as-tallest-building-in-america |archivedate=2015-09-04 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url = http://time.com/3553897/one-world-trade-center-freedom-tower-opens-doors-new-york-city-911/|title = One World Trade Center Opens Its Doors|last = Iyengar|first = Rishi|date = 2014-11-03|work = TIME.com|access-date = 2015-01-12|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20170505082946/http://time.com/3553897/one-world-trade-center-freedom-tower-opens-doors-new-york-city-911/|archive-date = 2017-05-05|dead-url = no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Lower Manhattan: Current Construction|url=http://www.lowermanhattan.info/construction/project_updates/|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110914070256/http://www.lowermanhattan.info/construction/project_updates/|archivedate=2011-09-14|publisher=Lower Manhattan Construction Command Center|accessdate=2011-09-08|dead-url=yes}}</ref>
2008年至2011年擔任紐約港務局和新澤西州執行董事的克里斯多福·O·沃德（Christopher O. Ward)是襲擊事件的倖存者，他因讓事件現場的建設重回正軌而受到讚譽。<ref>{{cite web |url=https://twintowersalliance.com/Ward_1-30-09.pdf |title=Transcript: Friday, 1/30/09 {{!}} Chris Ward, Executive Director of the Port Authority of New York and New Jersey |website=twintowersalliance.com |access-date=2021-09-12 |archive-date=2022-05-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220512070859/https://twintowersalliance.com/Ward_1-30-09.pdf }}</ref>

2016年3月3日，原临时车站，以世界貿易中心交通樞紐（World Trade Center Transportation Hub）為名重新啟用。新車站由西班牙建築師[[聖地牙哥·卡拉特拉瓦|聖地牙哥·卡拉特拉]]瓦設計，此外在原柏樹街155號的[[世界贸易中心圣尼古拉国家朝圣地|希臘正教會聖尼古拉堂]]，是襲擊事件中除世界貿易中心以外唯一完全被摧毀的建築物，後在紐約與新澤西港務局的開發下進行重建工程，並在2021年9月11日，即事發20週年後舉辦點燈儀式，預估在2022年4月完工。<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|last=Paolicelli|first=Alyssa|date=10 September 2021|title=New St. Nicholas Greek Orthodox Church lights up for first time for 9/11|url=https://www.ny1.com/nyc/all-boroughs/news/2021/09/11/saint-nicholas-greek-orthodox-church-and-national-shrine-lights-up-first-time-for-september-11th|url-status=live|access-date=2021-09-12|website=www.ny1.com|publisher=[[NY1|NY1]]|language=en|archive-date=2022-05-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220512070848/https://www.ny1.com/nyc/all-boroughs/news/2021/09/11/saint-nicholas-greek-orthodox-church-and-national-shrine-lights-up-first-time-for-september-11th}}</ref>
==纪念==
{{Further|九一一国家纪念博物馆}}
