[[File:US_Coast_Guard_photo_140911-G-ZV332-011_Ellis_Island_American_flag_honors_9_11_victims.jpg|left]]將[[美國國旗|美國國旗]][[降半旗|降半旗]]以示憑弔。]]
袭击第二天，世界各地纪念和守夜林立，[[原爆点|原爆点]]四周贴满了去世和失踪者的照片。一位目击者称自己“无法摆脱无辜丧生者的面孔。他们的照片到处都是，贴满了电话亭、街灯、地铁外墙。这一切让我想起大葬礼，人们肃穆、哀悼，但很友善。之前，纽约给我的感觉是冷漠；如今，人们伸出援手，互助扶持。”<ref>{{cite web|last=Sigmund|first=Pete|title=Crews Assist Rescuers in Massive WTC Search|url=http://www.constructionequipmentguide.com/Crews-Assist-Rescuers-in-Massive-WTC-Search/1531/|publisher=Construction Equipment Guide|accessdate=2011-09-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110815180434/http://www.constructionequipmentguide.com/Crews-Assist-Rescuers-in-Massive-WTC-Search/1531/|archive-date=2011-08-15|dead-url=no}}</ref>

第一个纪念方式是投射灯柱，有88个探照灯安在世贸中心塔基上。<ref>{{cite news| title = Tribute in light to New York victims| publisher = BBC News| date = 2002-03-06| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/americas/1857699.stm| accessdate = 2012-04-01| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20120129170013/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/americas/1857699.stm| archive-date = 2012-01-29| dead-url = no}}</ref>纽约展开了世贸中心纪念馆设计竞赛，海选精品。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://wtcsitememorial.org/about.html |title=About the World Trade Center Site Memorial Competition |accessdate=2011-09-04 |publisher=World Trade Center Site Memorial Competition |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181225172259/http://wtcsitememorial.org/about.html%20 |archive-date=2018-12-25 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>2006年8月，《倒映虚空》（Reflecting Absence）脱颖而出，主张在塔基上建造一对镜面池塘，环刻故人姓名。<ref>{{cite news| agency = Associated Press| title = WTC Memorial Construction Begins| publisher = [[CBS_News|CBS News]]| date = 2006-03-06| url = http://www.cbsnews.com/stories/2006/03/13/national/main1393070.shtml| accessdate = 2011-09-04| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20181225172053/https://www.cbsnews.com/news/wtc-memorial-construction-begins/| archive-date = 2018-12-25| dead-url = no}}</ref>2006年8月，世贸中心纪念基金会和纽约与新泽西港务局开始大规模建设[[九一一国家纪念博物馆|纪念馆和博物馆]]。<ref>{{cite web |last=Schuerman |first=Matthew |url=http://www.observer.com/2007/memorial-name-changes-gets-longer |title=Trade Center Memorial Name Changes, Gets Longer | The New York Observer |publisher=Observer.com |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120226185241/http://www.observer.com/2007/memorial-name-changes-gets-longer |archivedate=2012-02-26 |accessdate=2017-02-23 }}</ref>2011年9月11日，袭击十周年纪念活动在纪念馆举行，该馆次日向公众开放。博物馆于2014年5月15日完成，21日开放。

2008年，五角大楼纪念馆完工，并于遇袭七周年当日开放。<ref>{{cite news |first=Nick |last=Miroff |title=Creating a Place Like No Other |url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2008/09/10/AR2008091000018.html |work=The Washington Post |publisher=[[The_Washington_Post_Company|The Washington Post Company]] |date=2008-09-11 |accessdate=2011-09-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181225172450/http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2008/09/10/AR2008091000018.html%20 |archive-date=2018-12-25 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |first=Nick |last=Miroff |title=A Long-Awaited Opening, Bringing Closure to Many |url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2008/09/11/AR2008091100579.html?hpid=topnews |work=The Washington Post |publisher=The Washington Post Company |date=2008-09-12 |accessdate=2011-09-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110820073711/http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2008/09/11/AR2008091100579.html?hpid=topnews |archive-date=2011-08-20 |dead-url=no }}</ref>纪念馆包括184个面向五角大楼的长凳。<ref name="dwyer-may2007">{{cite news| last=Dwyer| first=Timothy| url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2007/05/25/AR2007052502284.html| title=Pentagon Memorial Progress Is Step Forward for Families| date=2007-05-26| work=The Washington Post| accessdate=2011-09-04| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110820073820/http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2007/05/25/AR2007052502284.html| archive-date=2011-08-20| dead-url=no}}</ref>2001至2002年间，五角大楼进行修复，并在77次航班撞击的位置建了一个小教堂和室内纪念馆。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.defenselink.mil/photos/newsphoto.aspx?newsphotoid=4018 |title=DefenseLINK News Photos – Pentagon's America's Heroes Memorial |publisher=Department of Defense |accessdate=2011-09-04 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091130081905/http://www.defenselink.mil/photos/newsphoto.aspx?newsphotoid=4018 |archivedate=2009-11-30 }}</ref>

尚克斯维尔计划建立[[联合航空93号国家纪念馆|联合航空93号国家纪念馆]]，围上树丛，在风铃刻上故人姓名。<ref>{{cite news| agency = Associated Press| title = Sept. 11 Flight 93 Memorial Design Chosen| publisher = [[Fox_News_Channel|Fox News]]| date = 2005-09-08| url = http://www.foxnews.com/story/0,2933,168821,00.html| accessdate = 2011-09-04| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20110818141726/http://www.foxnews.com/story/0,2933,168821,00.html| archive-date = 2011-08-18| dead-url = yes}}</ref>临时纪念馆位于事故地点{{convert|500|yd|0}}处。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nps.gov/flni|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080411125737/http://www.nps.gov/flni|archivedate=2008-04-11|title=Flight 93 Memorial Project|publisher=Flight 93 Memorial Project / National Park Service|accessdate=2011-09-04|dead-url=no}}</ref>
纽约市消防员捐献了一个用世贸钢材制作的十字架，立在类似五角大楼形状的底子上，<ref name='ap2008-08-24'>{{cite news | last = Nephin | first = Dan | title = Steel cross goes up near flight's 9/11 Pa. crash site | date = 2008-08-24 | agency = Associated Press | url = http://global.christianpost.com/news/steel-cross-installed-near-flight-93-site-in-pa-33978/ | accessdate = 2011-09-05 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20111021140020/http://global.christianpost.com/news/steel-cross-installed-near-flight-93-site-in-pa-33978/ | archive-date = 2011-10-21 | dead-url = yes }}</ref>并于2008年8月25日安装在消防局外。<ref>{{cite news|last=Gaskell|first=Stephanie|title=Pa. site of 9/11 crash gets WTC beam|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2008/05/05/us/05memorial.html|date=2008-08-25|work=New York Daily news|accessdate=2011-09-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110513193737/http://www.nytimes.com/2008/05/05/us/05memorial.html|archive-date=2011-05-13|dead-url=no}}</ref>多地建立了纪念馆。逝者家属、相关组织建立了许多奖学金和慈善基金。<ref>{{cite news| last=Fessenden| first=Ford| title=9/11; After the World Gave: Where $2 Billion in Kindness Ended Up| url=https://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9505E3DB1030F93BA25752C1A9649C8B63| work=The New York Times| date=2002-11-18| accessdate=2011-09-04| archive-date=2020-11-11| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201111211025/https://www.nytimes.com/2002/11/18/giving/9-11-after-the-world-gave-where-2-billion-in-kindness-ended-up.html| dead-url=no}}</ref>

纽约市每年都会在肃穆的音乐背景下诵读故人姓名。美国总统出席了五角大楼的纪念活动，<ref>{{cite news | url=http://cityroom.blogs.nytimes.com/2010/09/11/at-a-memorial-ceremony-loss-and-tension/?hp | work=The New York Times | title=At a Memorial Ceremony, Loss and Tension | first=Andy | last=Newman | date=2010-09-11 | access-date=2017-02-23 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181225172703/https://cityroom.blogs.nytimes.com/2010/09/11/at-a-memorial-ceremony-loss-and-tension/?hp%20 | archive-date=2018-12-25 | dead-url=no }}</ref>要求美国人遵守爱国日（Patriot Day），肃静默哀。宾夕法尼亚州尚克斯维尔举行了小型纪念活动，通常由总统夫人出席。

[[File:US_Navy_090720-N-7090S-021_Steel_recovered_from_the_World_Trade_Center_is_displayed_aboard_the_amphibious_transport_dock_ship_Pre-Commissioning_Unit_(PCU)_New_York_(LPD_21).jpg|缩略图]]

为纪念该事件，联合航空93号班机的出发机场——[[纽瓦克国际机场|纽瓦克国际机场]]随后改名为纽瓦克'''自由'''国际机场。在[[圣安东尼奥级两栖船坞运输舰|圣安东尼奥级两栖船坞运输舰]]中，有三艘舰的命名是为了纪念911事件：編號LPD-21的[[纽约号两栖运输船坞舰|纽约号]]（USS New York LPD-21）以世贸中心所在地命名，且其船身有约7.5吨钢料是回收自倒塌的世贸中心大楼，主要用于制造舰艏部分；編號LPD-24的{{link-en|阿靈頓號兩棲運輸船塢艦|USS Arlington (LPD-24)|阿靈頓號}}（USS Arlington LPD-24）以遭客機撞擊的[[五角大楼|五角大楼]]所在的[[阿灵顿县_(弗吉尼亚州)|阿灵顿县]]命名；編號LPD-25的{{link-en|薩默塞特號兩棲運輸船塢艦|USS Somerset (LPD-25)|薩默塞特號}}（USS Somerset LPD-25）以聯合航空93號班機墜毀地點的[[萨默塞特县_(宾夕法尼亚州)|萨默塞特县]]命名。

